# Custom sort order: Collection? / Field? / Documents? · Issue #179 · typesense/typesense
created: 2021-01-07, last updated: 2025-07-24, [Read more](https://github.com/typesense/typesense/issues/179)

We currently only support the ability to override rankings based on search query, using the
```
[overrides](https://typesense.org/docs/0.18.0/api/#curation)
```
endpoint.
Now, if we support overrides based on
```
filter_by
```
values, would that be a better solve for your use case?
For eg, something like this:
```
override_1 = {
"rule": {
"filter_by": "category:mens_socks",
},
"includes": [
{"id": "422", "position": 1},
{"id": "54", "position": 2}
],
"excludes": [
{"id": "287"}
]
}
override_2 = {
"rule": {
...
},
"includes": [
...
{"id": "54", "position": 6}
],
"excludes": [
{"id": "287"}
]
}
```
And then any time you run a search query with a
```
filter_by
```
parameter defined in the override rule, those ranking will be used.
...
Documents not containing my requested
...
```
...
```

